SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 64
BY SENATOR BOUDREAUX
CONDOLENCES. Expresses sincere and heartfelt condolences on the passing of former
Louisiana Medicaid Director Josephine Ruth Kennedy.
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To express sincere and heartfelt condolences on the passing of former Louisiana Medicaid
3 Director Josephine Ruth Kennedy.
4 WHEREAS, it is with profound sorrow that the people of Louisiana have learned of
5 the passing of Josephine Ruth Kennedy, who departed this life peacefully at her home on
6 Friday, March 20, 2026, at the age of seventy-one; and
7 WHEREAS, Josephine Ruth Kennedy, lovingly known by all as Ruth Kennedy, was
8 born on December 1, 1954, in Independence, Louisiana, and was raised in Springfield on her
9 family's strawberry farm by her parents, Josephine and Walter Kennedy, in a close-knit
10 family that instilled in her the values of faith, service, and hard work that would guide her
11 throughout her life; and
12 WHEREAS, she graduated from Springfield High School in 1972, attended Oregon
13 Bible College from 1972 to 1974, and continued her education at Southeastern Louisiana
14 University from 1975 to 1979, preparing herself for a life of service to others; and
15 WHEREAS, Ruth Kennedy was a lifelong and devoted member of Blood River
16 Church of God, where she faithfully shared her faith, taught others, and demonstrated
17 compassion and generosity through her service to her church and community, touching
18 countless lives through her kindness and encouragement; and
