1 WHEREAS, she built an honorable and distinguished career spanning more than
2 forty years in public service with the Louisiana Department of Health, dedicating herself to
3 ensuring that families across Louisiana had access to essential health services and
4 opportunities for care; and
5 WHEREAS, through her leadership, innovation, and determination, she helped lead
6 major initiatives to expand health coverage and improve care delivery across the state,
7 including the implementation and expansion of the Louisiana Children's Health Insurance
8 Program (LaCHIP) and the development of Bayou Health, and was known for personally
9 traveling throughout the state to assist families in obtaining health coverage; and
10 WHEREAS, Ruth Kennedy was promoted to serve as Louisiana Medicaid Director,
11 where she oversaw a program that supported more than one million Louisianans and guided
12 efforts to expand coverage to an additional four hundred thousand working adults who
13 otherwise had limited access to health care; and
14 WHEREAS, her tireless dedication and expertise earned her widespread respect from
15 colleagues, policymakers, and healthcare providers across Louisiana and throughout the
16 nation, and in recognition of her exemplary service to the citizens of Louisiana, she was
17 honored with the prestigious "Dunbar Award" in 2015, the highest honor bestowed upon
18 classified state employees; and
19 WHEREAS, after retiring from state government in 2017, Ruth Kennedy continued
20 her work to improve health care access and policy by joining Southern Strategy Group,
21 where she assisted providers and pharmacies, helped streamline eligibility verification
22 programs, supported hospital systems, and worked to expand opportunities for care and
23 professional training for pharmacy technicians across the state and beyond; and
24 WHEREAS, throughout her life, Ruth Kennedy was known as a pioneer who was
25 fearless, resourceful, and deeply compassionate, guided by her unwavering faith and
26 commitment to helping individuals and families who otherwise would have gone without
27 needed care; and
28 WHEREAS, Ruth Kennedy is survived by her sisters, Betty Gay Rena and Regina
29 McCord; her brother, Joseph Kennedy and his wife, Sharon; her sister-in-law, Loretta
30 Kennedy; her special cousin, Sharon Irby Derbins; her special niece, Kay Kinchen; and
