1 many loving nieces and nephews; and
2 WHEREAS, she was preceded in death by her parents, Josephine and Walter
3 Kennedy; her siblings, Juanita Kennedy Kinchen and Curtis Kennedy; and her
4 brothers-in-law, Willie Kinchen and Woody Rena; and
5 WHEREAS, Ruth Kennedy will be remembered for her unwavering faith, her
6 servant's heart, and her lifelong dedication to improving the lives of others, and her legacy
7 of compassion, leadership, and public service will continue to inspire generations of
8 Louisianans.
9 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
10 does hereby express its sincere and heartfelt condolences on the passing of former Louisiana
11 Medicaid Director Josephine Ruth Kennedy and does hereby recognize and honor her
12 remarkable career of public service and her enduring contributions to the health and welfare
13 of the people of Louisiana.
14 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to the
15 family of Josephine Ruth Kennedy and to the Louisiana Department of Health as an
16 expression of the Senate's deepest sympathy and respect.
